description: Gungnir Resources Inc., a junior mineral exploration company, engages in the acquisition, evaluation, and exploration of mineral properties. The company primarily explores for gold, nickel, copper, cobalt, and base metals. Its key project is the Knaften property that covers an area of approximately 4,887 hectares located in northern Sweden. The company was formerly known as Anglo Swiss Resources Inc. and changed its name to Gungnir Resources Inc. in April 2014. Gungnir Resources Inc. was founded in 1966 and is based in Surrey, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Jari  Paakki B.Sc., M.Sc., P. Geo., P.Geo.
